The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for image authentication, which involves techniques related to computer vision (CV) and machine learning (MM). The security aspect of the proposed approach suggests that it may belong to the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the use of neural networks and non-linear techniques indicates that it may also belong to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the focus on grayscale images suggests that it may also belong to the category of Computer Vision (cs.CV).
